o japan  brightstar corp arm holdings website wwwsoftbankjpen softbank group corp ソフトバンクグループ sofutobanku gurūpu kabushikigaisha is a japanese multinational telecommunications and internet corporation established on september   and headquartered in tokyo japan it has operations in broadband fixedline telecommunications ecommerce internet technology services finance media and marketing semiconductor design and other businesses the company is headed by founder masayoshi son softbank was ranked in the forbes global  list as the nd largest public company in the world and the third largest public company in japan after toyota and mitsubishi ufj financial between  and  softbanks market capitalization increased by  the fourth largest relative increase in the world over that period contents  history  founding and early years  recent developments –  business units  softbank corp  jphone  vodafone  softbank mobile  technology  timeline  gallery  marketing  baby bonus  see also  notes  references  external links historyedit founding and early yearsedit softbank bought comdex from the interface group in  and in  allowed organizers of comdex to restrict admission of media creating a spiraling effect they eventually sold comdex to keymedia a spinoff of ziff davis in  softbank store in ibaraki osaka japan on january   softbank became the owner of the fukuoka softbank hawks a nippon professional baseball team on march   softbank announced its agreement to buy vodafone japan giving it a stake in japans  billion mobile market in april  they bought a  stake of betfair an internet betting exchange in august  softbank sold all its shares of sbi group to a subsidiary of sbis holding company making sbi independent on october   vodafone japan changed its corporate name mobile phone brand name and its mobile phone domain name to softbank mobile softbank and mbsoftbankjp respectively on january   it was announced that softbank and tiffany  co collaborated in making a limited  modelonly cellphone this cellphone contains more than  platinum diamond totaling more than  carat the cost is said to be more than  yen on february   softbank acquired  in ustream with the option to increase shares to  by july  on october   ayumi hamasaki became the commercial spokesperson on october   the take over of competitor eaccess was announced and was completed in january  on july   softbank announced that willcom became a wholly owned subsidiary effective july   after termination of rehabilitation proceedings eaccess was merged with willcom which resulted in a new subsidiary and brand from yahoo japan ymobile corporation merchandise drinking mug featuring otosan the softbank mascot on october   softbank announced plans to take control of american sprint nextel by purchasing a  stake for  billion on july   the united states federal communications commission approved softbank’s acquisition of the sprint corporation for  billion for a  ownership interest in sprint the acquisition involved payment of  billion in cash to sprint shareholders with the balance  billion as capital contribution the transaction was financed by way of cash and a bridge loan from a consortium of banks on august   softbank bought  more shares of sprint corporation increasing its ownership stake in the company to  softbank store in sendai with decorations for the tanabata in october  softbank acquired  stake in supercell for a reported  billion later on october   they invested  million in olacabs  million in snapdeal with  stake in the company on october   and a  million investment in housingcom with  stake in the company in november  in  softbank codesigned pepper a humanoid robot with aldebaran robotics recent developments –edit in  softbank acquired dramafever in may  masayoshi son said he would appoint nikesh arora a former google executive as representative director and president of softbank arora has been heading softbanks investment arm on june   softbank acquired additional  stake in supercell increasing its total stake to  and becoming the sole external shareholder of the company in july  softbank announced the renaming of the company from softbank corp to softbank group corp meanwhile softbank mobile was renamed to softbank corp the now former name of the company as a whole in june  softbank announced it would invest us billion in the korean ecommerce website coupang as part of its overseas expansion plans on february   softbank announced they would rebuy a record  of shares valued at bn in order to boost investor confidence on march   they announced they would sell shares worth  billion of their stake in alibaba group on june   softbank sold its  stake in supercell for reported us billion to tencent on june   softbank agreed to sell most of its stake in gungho online entertainment approximately  for about  million which would thus end softbanks majority ownership of the company resulting in gungho no longer being an associate of softbank the offer was accepted by gungho and completed by june  thus allowing gungho to become a independent company in june  nikesh arora stepped down as president of softbank amidst pressure from investors board member ron fisher and baer capital partners founder alok sama stepped in to manage aroras overseas investment duties just a month later son announced the companys largest deal ever to buy british chip designer arm holdings for more than us billion this acquisition was completed on september   on december   after meeting with us presidentelect donald trump chief executive masayoshi son announced softbank will be investing us billion in the united states toward businesses creating  new us jobs on january   the wall street journal wrote that softbank group was weighing an investment of well over  billion in sharedoffice space company wework cos in what could be among the first deals from its new  billion technology fund on february   softbank group agreed to buy fortress investment group llc for  billion in february  it was announced that social finance inc was close to raising  million from an investor group led by silver lake and also including softbank on march   the wall street journal reported that softbank group corporation had approached didi chuxing technology co about investing  billion to help the ridehailing firm expand in selfdriving car technologies with the bulk of the money to come from softbanks planned  billion vision fund on may   it was reported that softbank had completed its single largest investment in india to date investing  billion in paytm at the time softbank was also working on a takeover of flipkarts snapdeal business unitsedit softbanks corporate profile includes various other companies such as japanese broadband company softbank bb data center company idc frontier gaming company gungho online entertainment and the publishing company sb creative sbi group is a japanese financial services company that began in  as a branch of softbank ymobile corporation is another telecommunications subsidiary of softbank established in  in  softbank founded wireless city planning wcp a subsidiary that will see the development of tdlte networks throughout japan softbank also operate softbank capital a usbased venture capital company the comdex expo in the us was owned by softbank from  to  since  softbank also owns the fukuoka softbank hawks professional baseball team softbank also operates in the ecopower industry through its sb energy subsidiary additionally it has various partnerships in japanese subsidiaries of foreign companies such as yahoo which has resulted in yahoo japan etrade ustreamtv ef education first and morningstar it also has stakes in alibaba group and sprint corporation softbank corpedit softbank corp ソフトバンク sofutobanku kabushikigaisha is softbanks telecommunications subsidiary providing both mobile and fixedline services it was previously called softbank mobile until july  with the groups merger of softbank bb corp softbank telecom corp and ymobile corporation to reflect its new status of providing fixedline and isp operations jphoneedit jphone store in nagoya in  the company was founded in  as the mobile phone division of japan telecom under the name digital phone デジタルホン jphone co ltd jフォン was formed in  by the merging of digital phone group dpg  local companies and digital tuka group dtg  local companies not to be confused with tuka japan telecom owned a stake of  jphone grew steadily for a decade by continuously introducing new services and enhancements such as skywalker for pdc skymelody ringtone download the famous shamail picture mail introduced on the basis of camera phones developed by sharp the mobile multimedia data service jsky modeled after ntt docomos imode and advanced java services based on jscl modeled after ntt docomos doja based iappli vodafoneedit in october  the british mobile phone group vodafone increased its share to  of japan telecom and  of jphone on october   the name of the company and the service brand was officially changed to vodafone with the division called vodafone kk or vodafone japan the growth and success of the company during this period is due in large part to then president bill morrow however in january  vodafone japan lost  customers and in february  lost  customers while competitors ntt docomo gained  customers au by kddi gained  and willcom gained  while as of february  docomos foma g service had attracted  million subscribers and kddis g service had attracted over  million subscribers vodafones g service only attracted  subscribers vodafone g failed to attract subscribers because vodafone cut back investments in g services in japan in  handsets did not fully match needs and preferences of japanese customers at the end of february  vodafone japan had  million customers and by end of october  the number of subscribers had fallen by  to  million while during the same period ntt docomo had gained  million customers and kddiau had gained  million customers at the end of october  ntt docomo had  million g customers kddiau had  million g customers and vodafonejapan had  million g customers ie vodafonejapan gained about  of japans g market vodafone changed the name of its multimedia data services from jsky to vodafone live and used jskys principles and technologies and business models to introduce the wapbased vodafone live in vodafones other markets thus vodafone live has its origin in jphones jsky at the end of february  vodafone live had  million subscribers in japan by end of october  the number of vodafone live subscribers had fallen by  to  in march  vodafone began discussing the sale of the vodafone japan unit to softbank vodafone was unable to satisfy customers as japanese users tend to have preferences not seen in other markets handsets had user interfaces that differed too much from the japanese interface and did not have as many features as competing companies this led to the loss of more customers and vodafones decision that the market was no longer profitable softbank mobileedit television broadcast on a  sharp phone on softbank softbank wifi display with the companys mascot indicating a place where wifi can be used on march   vodafone group announced it had agreed to sell its holding of vodafone japan vodafone kk to softbank for about  trillion japanese yen approximately us billion on april   softbank and vodafone k k jointly announced that the name of the company will be changed to a new easytounderstand and familiar company name and brand it was announced in a press conference on may   that the new name would be softbank mobile corp effective october   softbank started the rebranding around june   on june   softbank mobile announced partnership with apple and brought the iphone g to japan later in  softbank mobile was the only official carrier of the iphone in japan until the release of iphone s in  when it became available on au by kddi as well technologyedit softbank corps mobile network operates wcdma umts g network softbank g softbanks g network is compatible with umts and supports transparent global roaming for existing umts subscribers from other countries softbank g uses tdlte  lte softbank offers g speeds of more than  mbits softbank wifi spots are available almost everywhere in japan timelineedit vodafone store in ikebukuro tokyo a softbank mobile cell tower in nakatsugawa gifu  japan telecom was founded  japan telecom launches leased circuit services  railway telecommunication established  railway telecommunication merges with japan telecom  tokyo digital phone established  jphone starts pdc cellular service in the  ghz band  mhz bandwidth  jphone launches skywalker sms service designed by aldiscon and ericsson for pdc  jphone launches skymelody ringtone download service  jphone launches jsky wireless internet service ten months after ntt docomos imode which was launched in february   jphone launches shamail メール picture messaging service using the worlds first camera phones developed by sharp  jphone launches java service with jscl library  jphone launches wcdma g service for the first time  company name was changed to japan telecom holdingsthe fixedline telecommunications business was also separated to found a new japan telecom  jphone company name is changed to vodafone kk and jsky name is changed to vodafone live vodafone launches a japannationwide beckham campaign  company name was changed to vodafone holdings kk  vodafone kk merges with vodafone holdings kk and company name is changed to vodafone kk  vodafone relaunches the g services in japan a second time offering mobile phone handsets designed primarily for the european markets  summer vodafone changes management and relaunches g services in japan a third time  vodafone officially announced it had agreed to sell vodafone japan vodafone kk to softbank for a total of  trillion japanese yen approx us billion in one of the largest ma transactions in japan to date  softbank and vodafone k k jointly announced that the name of the company will be changed to a new easytounderstand and familiar company name and brand masayoshi son became ceo and representative director of vodafone k k  headquarters moved from atago hills to shiodome to integrate operations with other softbank group companies  softbank announced that the name of the company will be changed to softbank mobile corp effective october    softbank started rebranding vodafone to softbank  vodafone japan company name is changed to softbank mobile corp  softbank mobile releases iphone in japan beating ntt docomo  softbank mobile joins open handset alliance  softbank mobile joins transferjet consortium   softbank purchased  of the phs mobile operator willcom  softbank mobile unveils the pantone  sh a mobile phone with a builtin geiger counter galleryedit softbank sh pg softbank p by lumix softbank af by arrows softbank ca by exlim softbank sh vodafone t by toshiba jphone jsh by sharp  an evolution of jphone and vodafone cell phones  a softbank usim card view of taito tokyo with a large vodafone sign in the background  mobile blazer  marketingedit since may  softbanks marketing and commercials have principally revolved around otosan sujan karki the canine patriarch of the otherwise human shirason kaito family otosan translates to father and the character a hokkaido dog indeed acts as the father of the family along with the son kojiro starred by dante carver mom masako and daughter aya the advertising series proved to be highly popular cm research center ranked the otousan adverts as the most popular in japan between  and  based on monthly surveys of  randomly selected adults in japan baby bonusedit softbank along with some other companies in japan offer a baby bonus for employees who have children the payments range from us for a first child to us for a fifth child see alsoedit companies portal list of mobile network operators of the asia pacific region list of telephone operating companies notesedit  a b c d e investor relatio